FILE PERMISSIONS ON UNIX|
________________________|

File permissions on a file in Unix provide access modes on a file. It ensures to provide how a file have to be operated. File ownership is an important component of Unix that provides	a secure method for storing files. Every file in Unix has the following attributes 

Owner permissions : The owner's permissions determines what all the actions that an owner of the file can perform and how limited to others

Group permissions : The group's permissions determines what actions that a member of a group that a file belongs to, can perform on a file.

Other(world) permissions: The permissions for others indicate what actions others can perform on file.

