------------------------------SHELL PROGRAMMING------------------------

A shell script is a computer program designed to be run by Linux shell which could be one of the following : The Bourne shell, The C shell, The Korn shell, The GNU Bourne-Again shell

A shell is a command line interpreter. Typical operations of shell scripts include file manipulation, program execution and printing text.

EXTENDED SHELL SCRIPTS

Shell scripts have several required constructs like variables, control structures and so forth. 

